items.content:
Hi kids,

In this Wikiwijs you can find all the information you need for Thema 7: Eigen Onderzoek. First click on the tab called Course Outline (lesplanner) to see which tasks you're going to work on during the next three weeks. This theme is a bit different because of the 'roostervrije weken' draft.

Have fun!
Your teachers.

heading.content: Final task 'High Tea & Thank you speeches'

items.content:
Project - Thank you Speech/High Tea MAVO/HAVO/VWO

This school year you have been working on various language skills. In this final English project you are going to organise a high-tea for your classmates. During this high tea we will serve and eat some typical English snacks such as scones with clotted cream and marmalade, and cucumber sandwiches. While we are having our high tea we're going to thank our classmates for the amazing school year. You are going to give a thank-you-speech which you're going to write somewhere during this week. Have fun!

Task 1

Preparation
- Samen met een klasgenoot vorm je een duo. Samen zoeken jullie uit welke gerechten geserveerd worden tijdens een typische High Tea. Deze gerechten worden met een bordstift op het whiteboard geschreven (zorg dat gerechten maar één keer op het bord staan).
- Ook ga je zelfstandig nadenken welke stamgroepgenoot en welke expert en/of mentor je zou willen bedanken in jouw speech. Geef dit ook door aan je expert.

Task
- Met de stamgroep besluiten we welk duo welke High Tea lekkernij gaat verzorgen. Zorg dat je portioneert op ongeveer 3 personen. Vergeet de lekkernij tijdens de High Tea niet mee te nemen!
- Schrijf je thank-you-speeches in het Engels eerst in klad voordat je aan het origineel begint. De speeches heb je de volgende les uitgeprint en in een enveloppe bij je. Zorg dat de naam van degene waarvoor je je speech hebt geschreven voorop de enveloppe staat. Je hebt dus in totaal twee enveloppen met in ieder een speech; één voor een stagmroepgenoot en één voor een expert/mentor. Je mag de speech typen maar ga voor een originele versie helemaal los op mooi briefpapier en schrijf de speech in je beste handschrift.
- Je speeches bevatten ten minste de volgende onderdelen:
* Je bedankt een stamgroepgenoot voor het schooljaar. Je vertelt een korte anekdote over wat jullie dit schooljaar hebben meegemaakt en waarom je hem wil bedanken (denk aan je kennis van de Past Simple, Present Perfect en Past Continuous).
* Je bedankt een expert en/of mentor voor het schooljaar. Je vertelt een korte anekdote over wat jullie dit schooljaar hebben meegemaakt en waarom je hem wil bedanken (denk aan je kennis van de Past Simple, Present Perfect en Past Continuous).
- Zorg dat de speech ongeveer een half A4-tje lang is. Je hoeft de speech niet uit je hoofd te leren, maar een aantal van jullie gaat hem wel voorlezen.

Task 2

Preparation
- Zorg dat je thuis de lekkernij hebt voorbereid die we op de dag van de High Tea tijdens de les kunnen opeten. We hebben een koelkast tot onze beschikking in de keuken, maar overleg dit eerst met je expert en met Roel. We kunnen geen gebruik maken van de keuken van Roel (oven, bestek e.d.) of de magnetron in het lerarenkeukentje.
- Zorg dat je thank-you-speeches thuis afgemaakt zijn. Ook zorg je dat je de speeches op papier bij je hebt en in verschillende enveloppes hebt gestopt (één voor je stamgroepgenoot en één voor je expert/mentor). Tip: plak de enveloppe nog niet dicht aangezien sommige de speech ook gaan voordragen.

Task
Op school lezen een aantal van jullie de speeches hardop voor. Tussendoor hebben we tijd om de lekkernijen te proeven.

Task 1: Listening & Watching - Why are the Brits so obsessed with tea?

What are you going to do?
In order to prepare well for your High Tea in week 3 you might want to find out why the British are so obsessed with tea. Watch the filmclip from the Wikwiwijspage and mark whether the statements are TRUE or FALSE. You are allowed to listen to the clip more than once.

Is this task mandatory?
No

When are you going to do this task?
We advise you to do this task in week 1 to understand more about the British culture and to learn why the Brits are mad about tea.

With whom are you going to do this task?
Do you find English difficult? Sign up for the English Expert's class to do this assignment with a little help from your peers and your expert. Are you up for the job yourself? Do the assignments during a time that suits you best. Either alone or together with a classmate. Finished? Sign up with an English Expert's class to receive the answers, or email your expert to receive the answers and check your work individually.

What do you need for this task?
You need your laptop and a set of earphones. You can find the full exercise and the filmclip on this English Wikiwijspage below.

items.caption: Why are Brits so obsessed with tea?

items.content:
A. Watch the video and mark the following statements as true (T) or false (F).

  1. Tea is the Brits' go-to solution for almost any scenario.
  2. The first thing you'll be probably asked by a Brit is if you would like a cup of coffee.
  3. The British love for tea dates back to 1650's.
  4. The British had been excluded from the tea exporting in the Med during the war with France and Spain.
  5. Due to the high tea prices, there was a rise in fake teas in the 1700's.
  6. Fake teas consisted of tea leaves mixed with other leaves.
  7. Tea was once the privilege of the rich people only.
  8. Afternoon tea is also known as high tea.
  9. Queen Victoria made the afternoon tea popular.
  10. Cream tea took its name because of the whipped cream served with this type of tea.
  11. The evening meal is often referred to as tea.
  12. Tea rooms became an integral part of the women's liberation movement.
  13. Churchill himself stated that "The tea is more important than war".
  14. 90% of tea comes in tea bags, which are an English invention.
  15. Tea bags were invented by a tea merchant who sent out tea samples to his costumers in silk sachets.

B. Match the teas with their descriptions.

A

Afternoon tea

1

It is a hot meal of meat pies, vegetables and bread, eaten at the end of the day.

B

Cream tea

2

Came about in around 1841 thanks to the Duchess of Bedford. It is made up of a selection of finger sandwiches, scones, pastries and home-made cakes.

C

High tea

3

It is served with scones, clotty cream and jam

heading.content: Task 2 - Writing your Thank You Speeches

items.content:
Task 2: High Tea & Thank-you-speeches - Writing your thank-you-speeches

What are you going to do?
This school year you have been working on various language skills. In this final English project you are going to organise a high-tea for your classmates. During this high tea we will serve and eat some typical English snacks such as scones with clotted cream and marmalade, and cucumber sandwiches. While we are having our high tea we're going to thank our classmates for the amazing school year. You are going to write two thank-you-speeches which some of you are going to recite during our high tea.

Is this task mandatory?
Yes

When are you going to do this task?
You're going to write your thank-you-speeches during week 1 and 2.

With whom are you going to do this task?
Do you find English difficult? Sign up for the English Expert's class to do this assignment with a little help from your peers and your expert. Are you up for the job yourself? Do the assignments during a time that suits you best. Make sure to write both a thank-you-speech for a classmate ÃÂ¡nd a thank-you-speech for a mentor or expert.

What do you need for this task?
You need your laptop and your knowledge of writing a speech. Think of all the grammar you learnt during year 2. Especially think of your knowledge of the Past Tenses (Past Simple, Present Perfect and Past Continuous). Finally, you need a printed copy of your thank-you-speech which you put in an enveloppe. Check if you've written the name of your classmate and the name of your mentor/expert for whom you've written your speech on the front of the enveloppe before you hand it in with your expert. You can find the full assignment on the English Wikiwijspage: https://maken.wikiwijs.nl/103131/Thema_7__Eigen_Onderzoek#!page-3336602

Task 3: Break-out kit - Escape your classroom using your knowledge of the 'Elements of a Story'

What are you going to do?
During theme 6: Arbeid en Productie you've read an English novel and you've had your first introduction to the 'Elements of a Story'. As mentioned during class you need this knowledge in year 3 when you're going to read a novel of your choice. To see whether you still remember all there is to know about this subject the year 4 havo/vwo students of DNS have created an assignment for you. By solving various puzzles and riddles you are going to escape your classroom using a break-out kit. This break-out kit has various locks on it which you need to open using your knowledge of reading.

Is this task mandatory?
No

When are you going to do this task?
You are able to do this task during week 2. There will be several different break-outs you can sign up for.

With whom are you going to do this task?
To make sure everyone can enjoy this exercise only 30 people can sign up for one break-out. Give some of the other students the possibility of enjoying this game as well so try to only sign up for this break-out activity once.

What do you need for this task?
You need your knowledge of 'Elements of a Story' so revise the powerpoint and your notes from theme 6: Arbeid en Productie. To help you out look at the English Wikiwijspage from theme 6 again: https://maken.wikiwijs.nl/100050/Thema_6__Arbeid_en_Productie#!page-3187486

heading.content: Task 4 - High Tea & Thank You Speeches

items.content:
Task 4: High Tea & Thank-you-speeches - High tea together with our classmates

What are you going to do?
This school year you have been working on various language skills. In this final English project you are going to organise a high-tea for your classmates. During this high tea we will serve and eat some typical English snacks such as scones with clotted cream and marmalade, and cucumber sandwiches. While we are having our high tea we're going to thank our classmates for the amazing school year. For this task we're going to listen to (some of) the written speeches and we're going to enjoy the home-made high tea treats.

Is this task mandatory?
Yes

When are you going to do this task?
We're going to have our high tea together with our full class during week 3. You will enjoy this high tea together with your own English expert (and your mentor).

With whom are you going to do this task?
You make your home-made, typical English high-tea treat together with another classmate. Make sure to portion your treat to 3 to 4 servings and let your own English expert now what you will be making.

What do you need for this task?
You need your special high-tea treat portioned to serve 3 to 4. You also need the printed copies of your thank-you-speeches. One copy of the thank-you-speech you've written for your classmate, one copy of the thank-you-speech you've written for your expert/mentor. These copies are neatly put into enveloppes and on the front of the enveloppe you've written the name of the receiver. You can find the full assignment on the English Wikiwijspage: https://maken.wikiwijs.nl/103131/Thema_7__Eigen_Onderzoek#!page-3336602

If you want to practise some more with the grammatical topics we've discussed (for example when they are difficult for you or to practise for a test), you have several options.

On this page there are a couple of website that you can use. With every website you can find a brief explanation of how they work.

On top of this page, you can also find a booklet with extra practise for all the grammatical topics we will learn in year 2. Download the booklet, print it, do the exercises and check them with your teacher to make sure you understand everything correctly.

Good luck!

https://www.duolingo.com/

Duolingo is an interactive learning format in which you train your listening and writing skills. You can practise a couple of minutes every day to quickly improve your English skills.

You can achieve goals and go to different levels to further improve your personal language skills.

Next to the desktop version, Duolingo also comes in an app for Android, iOS and Windows Phone.

A great way to improve your English and have fun at the same time!

www.ego4u.com

Go to this website and click the button ´Grammar´ in the top left corner.

On the grammar page you can find many different grammatical topics. Click on the one you would like to practise. You can first read a short explanation about the topic and then you can do various exercises. When you are finished you can immediately check your work and see if you have done them correctly or not.

http://www.englisch-hilfen.de/en/

Same as with the previous website, go to this website and click the button ´Grammar Explanation´. On this page, you can also find and explanation of all the different grammatical topics.

If you click on ´Grammar Exercises´ you can practise with all the different grammatical topics. Here you can also check your own work and see how you´ve done.

There is also a button ´Tests´ and ´Complex Test´.

https://quizlet.com/

Quizlet is a fun way to train new vocabulary. You can use the website on your laptop or you can download the app for your Android, Windows or Apple device.

Same as with WRTS, you can upload your words to Quizlet and save them so you can use them later. Them difference with WRTS is that with Quizlet, you can do various (interactive) games to study your new words.

A great way to get to know your new vocabulary!

If you're really good at English you might want to do more challenging exercises. That's why you can read the stories from the booklet (Short stories for Children). For every story you read you can do one of the exercises below.

Tell your Expert which story you've read, and hand in the exercises on paper.

Have fun!

Kies één opdracht uit de volgende lijst (eventueel op een apart vel papier). Je maakt deze opdracht in het Engels!.

a) Verzin een andere titel voor het verhaal en leg uit waarom die beter is.
b) Maak een tijdlijn waarin je de belangrijkste gebeurtenissen van het boek in de juiste volgorde plaatst.
c) Maak een advertentie voor iets dat in het boek voorkomt of dat ermee te maken heeft.
d) Schrijf een ander einde aan het verhaal (± 75 woorden).
e) Schrijf een stuk uit het dagboek van een hoofdpersoon (±75 woorden).
f) Schrijf een interview tussen jezelf en een hoofdpersoon. Schrijf ook de antwoorden van de hoofdpersoon op, zoals jij denkt dat die zullen zijn. In totaal schrijf je ± 5 vragen (en dus ook 5 antwoorden) op.
